{"lemma":"مِضْرَبٌ","slug":"مِضْرَبٌ","root":"ض.ر.ب","root_slug":"ض-ر-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ض-ر-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n25713"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B6%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bat, racket (club used for striking the ball in sports)","examples":[{"text":"مَثَلاً، عِنْدَنَا فِي كَالِيفُورْنِيَا لَوْ كَانَ دُكَّان يَبِيع مَضَارِب التِّنِس، فَإِنَّ جَارَهُ لَنْ يَبِيع مَضَارِب التِّنِس أَيْضًا.","english":"For example, in California, if it were a shop selling tennis rackets, its neighbour would not sell tennis rackets either."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Morphologically from the root ض ر ب (ḍ r b)."},"ipa":["/midˤ.rab/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n25713","headword_ar":"مِضْرَبٌ","root":"Drb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing with which one beats, strikes, smites,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hits;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which the action termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~arob","text_ar":"الضَّرْب"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is performed;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miDoraAbN","text_ar":"مِضْرَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A wooden instrument"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of mallet"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which the bow-string is struck in the operation of separating cotton."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b2-  And, (S, A, K,) as an epithet applied to a man, (S, A,) it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$adiydu","text_ar":"شَدِيدُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~arobi","text_ar":"الضَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who beats, strikes, smites,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hits, vehemently"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, O;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru AlD~arobi","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ الضَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[one"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who beats,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaruwbN","text_ar":"ضَرُوبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Dar~aAbN","text_ar":"ضَرَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DariybN","text_ar":"ضَرِيبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaribN","text_ar":"ضَرِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, K, TA. [But in none of these lexicons is this signification mentioned in such a manner as to show that it necessarily relates to any but the first of these words, namely,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miDorabN","text_ar":"مِضْرَبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": that it does so, however, is indicated by the measures of all of them.]) ―         -b3-  Also, (O, K, TA,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDoribN","text_ar":"مَضْرِبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":"and kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"r","text_ar":"ر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) [thus] written like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"majolisN","text_ar":"مَجْلِسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"by MF, and pronounced by the vulgar"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDorab","text_ar":"مَضْرَب"},{"kind":"text","text":", but both of these are [said to be] incorrect, (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent such as is called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qub~ap","text_ar":"قُبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a great"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tent of the kind called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fusoTaAT","text_ar":"فُسْطَاط"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (O, K, TA;) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fsTAT","text_ar":"فسطاط"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a king:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maDaAribu","text_ar":"مَضَارِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","A","K","TA","O","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}